title._content: Mrs Brightwell and her daughter, Amy Brightwell, of Parsley Bay, in Bundanoon. Unknown photographer, c. 1920

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales
tag.author: 29454428@N08

description._content: Miss Brightwell was a dressmaker with rooms in Dymocks Arcade, George Street, Sydney. Her letterhead read: "The knowledge that one is well dressed lends a grace to the carriage, a sparkle to the eye and a stimulus to the intellect". They were always dressed in the height of fashion - Bundanoon, NSW.
